{"comments":"Response — Collision response types and calculations.\n\n## Design Philosophy\n\nCollision response determines what happens when two objects collide.\nDifferent response types enable different physical behaviors:\n- Bounce: elastic collision (balls, pinball)\n- Slide: friction-based movement (boxes on ground)\n- Stick: adhesion (sticky surfaces, grappling hooks)\n\n## Bounded Design\n\nAll response parameters are bounded:\n- Restitution: 0-1 (inelastic to perfectly elastic)\n- Friction: 0-2 (frictionless to high friction)\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- Collision.Point (Point2D)\n- Collision.Contact (Contact)\n- Collision.Internal (clampUnit, maxNum)\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[75,17],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Physics/Collision/Response.purs","start":[75,3]},"title":"ResponseNone"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Record"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["restitution",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"tag":"REmpty"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[76,19],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Physics/Collision/Response.purs","start":[76,3]},"title":"ResponseBounce"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Record"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["friction",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"tag":"REmpty"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[78,18],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Physics/Collision/Response.purs","start":[78,3]},"title":"ResponseSlide"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[80,